<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05608</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING AN ADVANCED STUDIES DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM FOR EXCEPTIONAL EMPLOYEES FROM THE GOVERNMENT AND THE PRIVATE SECTOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : “ Pensionado Act Of 2017 ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : 
Seeks to reverse human capital flight or “brain drain” by establishing fellowship program for qualified Filipino professionals from the public and private sectors and for those who are self-employed; Intends to help Filipino professionals  obtain high-quality credentials, new skills, and expanded professional networks which will lead to the development of the country’s workforce as the returning scholars are expected to exert a broader influence by applying their knowledge and networks that they developed overseas. 	
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VARGAS, ALFRED D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-05-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Measure approved by the Committee on 2018-01-15</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2017-05-17</td></tr></table>